SIMPLE: surcingle
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Surcingle
<hw>Sur"cin`gle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>sursengle</ets>, OF. <ets>sursangle</ets>. See <er>Sur-</er>, and
<er>Cingle</er>, <er>Shingles</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A belt,
band, or girth which passes over a saddle, or over anything laid on a
horse's back, to bind it fast.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>The girdle of a cassock, by which
it is fastened round the waist.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Surcingled</ent>⟦br⟧
